        "content": "<p>I am trying to complete the proof of Lemma  <code>divand</code> and here's where I am at:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Coq\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">Lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">divand</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"k\">forall</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">m</span> <span class=\"n\">n</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">nat</span><span class=\"o\">),</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">%|</span> <span class=\"n\">n</span> <span class=\"o\">/\\</span> <span class=\"mi\">3</span> <span class=\"o\">%|</span> <span class=\"n\">m</span> <span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"mi\">6</span> <span class=\"o\">%|</span> <span class=\"n\">n</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">m</span> <span class=\"o\">.</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">Proof</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">m</span> <span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">.</span> <span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">H</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">H</span><span class=\"o\">.</span> <span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"o\">[/</span><span class=\"n\">dvdnP</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dvdnP</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">]].</span>\n<span class=\"k\">rewrite</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">apply</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dvdnP</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">Admitted</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In Lean, I would carry on by writing <code>use  (x * y)</code> and conclude by a computation. </p>\n<p>Is there something similar to the <code>use</code> tactic here? Also, what would be a more idiomatic way of writing the proof?</p>",
